data.title: Veeva Systems (NYSE: VEEV) to reveal Q3 fiscal results ending October 31, 2025 on November 20, 2025, with conference call at 2:00 p.m. PT.
data.description: In Pleasanton, California, Veeva Systems (NYSE: VEEV) is set to reveal its financial performance for the third quarter concluding on October 31, 2025, post-market closure on November 20, 2025. A conference call and webcast are scheduled for that day at 2:00 p.m. PT (5:00 p.m. ET) to discuss the results.

data.title: Synopsys to release Q4 and FY 2025 earnings on Dec 10, 2025, conference call at 2:00 pm PT.
data.description: Synopsys, Inc., based in Sunnyvale, California, will be releasing its financial results for the fourth quarter and fiscal year 2025 on December 10, 2025, after the market closes. The announcement will be made through a conference call scheduled at 2:00 p.m. Pacific Time (5:00 p.m. Eastern Time). Synopsys, listed on Nasdaq as SNPS, is anticipated to provide crucial insights into its performance during the mentioned periods.

data.title: ICF reports 14% revenue increase from commercial and government clients in Q3 2025, with commercial energy clients up 24%.
data.description: In the third quarter, revenues from commercial clients and state & local and international government clients saw a significant increase of 14%, contributing to 57% of total revenues. Specifically, revenues from commercial energy clients surged by 24%. The positive revenue growth was supported by a favorable mix and efficient cost management, leading to margin expansion. Despite the challenging market conditions, the company has managed to maintain its financial outlook.

data.title: Ball Corp (NYSE: BALL) appoints John E. Panichella, CEO of Solenis, to board of directors on 10/30/25. Expert in water treatment and specialty chemicals.
data.description: In Westminster, Colorado on October 30, 2025, Ball Corporation (NYSE: BALL) revealed the addition of John E. Panichella, the CEO of Solenis, to its board of directors. Panichella's expertise in water treatment and specialty chemicals industry enhances the board's composition. His appointment signifies a strategic move by Ball Corporation to leverage Panichella's experience in advancing their business objectives.

data.title: Illumina reports $1.08 billion revenue, flat from Q3 2024. GAAP operating margin 21.0%, non-GAAP 24.5%. EPS: $0.98 (GAAP), $1.34 (non-GAAP).
data.description: In the third quarter of 2025, the company reported a revenue of $1.08 billion, which was unchanged from the same period in 2024 when considering both reported and constant currency basis. The GAAP operating margin for Q3 2025 stood at 21.0%, with the non-GAAP operating margin at 24.5%. Additionally, the GAAP diluted earnings per share (EPS) for the third quarter of 2025 were $0.98, while the non-GAAP diluted EPS was $1.34. The cash provided by the company during this period was not specifically mentioned in the provided text.

data.title: ICF CFO Barry Broadus retiring in 2026 after 40 years; COO James Morgan to become CFO; Anne Choate as President.
data.description: Barry Broadus, a veteran finance professional, will be retiring as Chief Financial Officer in 2026 after dedicating 40 years to the industry. James Morgan, the current Chief Operating Officer, will assume the additional responsibility of CFO following Broadus' retirement. Concurrently, Anne Choate will take on the role of President. This transition is expected to take place on October 30, 2025, as per an official statement from ICF, a prominent global solutions and technology provider traded on the NASDAQ under the ticker symbol ICFI.

data.title: Tosoh Bioscience's GR01 HbA1c Analyzer receives FDA clearance for fast, accurate testing. #diagnostics #healthcare
data.description: A company based in Grove City, Ohio, Tosoh Bioscience, Inc., known for its expertise in clinical diagnostics, has recently obtained clearance from the U.S. FDA for its latest Tosoh Automated Glycohemoglobin Analyzer HLC®-723 GR01 (GR01) for conducting HbA1c tests. This advanced GR01 Analyzer is specifically crafted to enhance the process of HbA1c testing.

data.title: Columbia Banking System, Inc. reports Q3 2025 results with $96 million net income, $204 million operating income, and $0.40 and $0.85 EPS. CEO positive on progress.
data.description: In Tacoma, Washington, on October 30, 2025, a company reported its financial results with a net income of $96 million and operating net income of $204 million. The earnings per common share - diluted were $0.40, and operating earnings per common share - diluted were $0.85. The CEO commented on the third quarter performance, indicating significant progress and growth.

data.title: Harbor Group International buys Virginia Beach multifamily complex, expanding presence with Hampton Roads market.
data.description: Acquisition in Virginia Beach on Oct. 30, 2025, by Harbor Group International, LLC ("HGI") expands its presence in its home state and strengthens position in the Hampton Roads market. HGI, a privately-owned international real estate investment and management company, aims to grow its footprint through this strategic move. This development showcases significant growth potential for HGI within the local market, highlighting their commitment to enhancing their operations and investments.

data.title: Don Francisco's Coffee unveils Fall flavors: Maple Pecan, Caramel Spiced Rum. TV Host Sabrina Soto shares seasonal tips. Los Angeles, 30th Oct 2025.

data.title: Curis (NASDAQ: CRIS) to report Q3 2025 financial results on Nov 6th. Focus on emavusertib development.
data.description: In Lexington, Massachusetts, on October 30, 2025, Curis, Inc., a biotech firm (NASDAQ: CRIS), shared news about emavusertib (CA-4948), their IRAK4 inhibitor under development. The company revealed plans to disclose its financial performance for the third quarter of 2025.

data.title: Five local orgs in Northern & Central Calif. receive $500,000 grants for enviro projects from PG&E Foundation.
data.description: PG&E Corporation Foundation in Oakland, California, announced on October 30, 2025, that it is providing a total of $500,000 in grants to five local organizations in Northern and Central California. The recipients will use these funds to support environmental initiatives.
